      "content": "look i've had migraines for years and i know my body. last time i had a weird sensation like this it turned out to be just stress and it went away after i rested. if i take the sumatriptan now and just sleep it off, and if it's actually something bad i'll just go in the morning, right? im pretty sure it's just a bad flare up. is there any reason why taking the sumatriptan would be bad if it's just a migraine?",
